Everything in harness/ is licensed under MIT.

Reason: harness/grader loads the Mesen reference WebAssembly module at
runtime via wasmtime, in a separate address space and across a
published ABI (spec/ABI.md). That arm's-length aggregation is not a
combined work under GPL-3.0 §5, so the grader binary stays MIT even
though the reference module it loads is GPL-3.0.

